      "writtenOn": "2020-06-30T18:27:01Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Maybe it would be simpler to use flexbox here:\n\n  display: flex;\n  flex-direction: column;\n  align-items: center;\n  justify-content: space-between;\n\nThen, instead of hiding icons via the \"hidden\" attribute, we can use the visibility[1] CSS property, which hides an element without disrupting the flex layout:\n\n  .hidden {\n    visibility: hidden;\n  }\n\nThe main rationale is that the layout definition is centralized in one single place (i.e. the parent node) instead of being partially defined on the parent (position: relative) and on the child nodes (left/top/down properties).\n\n[1] https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/visibility",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 2,
        "startChar": 2,
        "endLine": 3,
        "endChar": 24
      },
      "revId": "dd0ee3bc4e993909dfcdea36ec5c28fdd0729ef1",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": true
